'''Biskupice''' (before 1927 ''Pišpeky'', 1773 ''Filakowska'';{{lang-hu|Fülekpüspöki}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
The village arose in the 12th century; it was first mentioned in records in 1294, when it belonged to the [[Esztergom Archbishopric]].

